  "texts": [
    "It can be observed that, thanks to the MHE-based state estimation, the output error is significantly reduced for both models M [1] and M [2], prior to being combined by the ensemble weighting.",
    "This paper addresses optimal control of complex systems operating under multiple conditions using ensemble models.",
    "Existing ensemble-based MPC frameworks typically rely on either fixed weights, which are suboptimal, or weights that 0 10 20 a) M [1] e [1] 0 20 40 60 0 10 20 b) M [2] Time [h]e [2]Fig. 4: Output error e [i] for model in open-loop (solid blue) and with MHE-based state estimation (dashed red).depend on system states and outputs, which are unavailable in prediction.",
    "In this work, we propose a novel combination rule for ensemble models based on the statistical Mahalanobis distance, allowing the ensemble weights to evolve over the prediction window solely as functions of the inputs.",
    "In addition, a new observer for ensemble models based on MHE is developed to provide accurate MPC state initialization."
  ]
